Figure 2.3: Top: Relative spectral distribution of emissions for Black Body Radiation at a given Temperature. The display colour of the curve approximates the perceived colour of this spectrum by the human eye. Compare the spectral output for a Halogen bulb around 3000K to 3500K vs Daylight at 6500K. Bottom: The same curve with interference calculated as a function of birefringence. Notice how the interference colours can appear different depending on the intial spectrum of light. These spectral curves have been generated in R from first principles and are converted into an estimation of the perceived colour using the pavo 2 package (Maia et al. 2013, 2019).



filtered = data_bbspec.filter(function(bbspectra) {
  return TempK == bbspectra.temperature;
})
filtered2 = data_intspec2.filter(function(intspectra2) {
  return TempK == intspectra2.temperature && biref2 == intspectra2.biref;
})



















